Manchester United are looking to swoop for two new midfield options while Arsenal have their eye on Juventus forward Lautaro Martinez in the latest Premier League transfer rumours from the media. United have their eyes trained on West Ham's 23-year-old Declan Rice who has reportedly turned down contract extension with the Hammers. The Red Devils are also said to be on the lookout for Ruben Neves for a potential summer bid for the Wolverhampton midfielder. On the flip side, Newcastle are said to be keen on acquiring the services of United's forward Jesse Lingard who is out of contract at Old Trafford.